    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, im seeing some weirdness in our ec2 instances. getting \"Connection reset by peer\" errors in the logs every few hours but it's totally intermittent. here is a snippet of the cloudwatch log:\n\n2023-10-24T14:22:01Z i-0a1234567890abcdef error: connection reset by peer (errno 104)\n2023-10-24T14:25:12Z i-0a1234567890abcdef error: connection reset by peer (errno 104)\n\nany idea if this could be a security group or NACL thing? or should i look at the app layer?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Connection reset by peer\" often suggests a disruption on the network or the destination host itself, so it could be several things. While security groups and NACLs can cause connectivity loss, they usually result in outright drops rather than resets, making the application layer a strong possibility. I recommend starting by checking the application logs and service status on the EC2 instance to see if any processes are crashing or timing out during those intervals.",
