    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the app logs and the service seems stable, no crashes. but i'm still seeing it happen. if it's not a drop, could it be an idle timeout issue? like maybe a load balancer or a firewall is killing the connection because it thinks it's inactive? how would i verify if that's what's happening?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An idle timeout is a very common cause for intermittent \"connection reset by peer\" errors. To verify this, check the configuration of any load balancers (like ELB/ALB) or proxies sitting in front of your EC2 instances for their configured idle timeout settings. You should also review any network firewalls between the client and the EC2 instance to see if they enforce connection limits. Matching the application's expected idle time with the intervening network device's timeout will confirm the issue.",
      "source": "target",
